SystemHardening \
     Minimize host OS footprint Reduce Attack Surface \
Common System Hardening \
Kubernertes cluster \
 > update hosts regularly  \
 > Remove unwanted utils \
 > Limit access with firewall rules \
 > log all system activities   \
Reduce host OS attack status \
 > create pod to use host namespace only if necessary \
 > Donot run containers in priviliged mode(priviliged = false, non-root user) \
 > Limit node access to users \
 > Remove unnecessary binaries and services \
 > control access using SSH, disable root and password-based logins \
 > Adding correct firewall rules to restrict host access on opened ports \
 > Preventing containers from loading unwanted kernel modules \
 > Identify and address open ports \
 > Restrict allowed host path using PodSecurityPolicies \
